Document: SphereMesh  
Path: godot/classes/class_spheremesh.rst  
Summary: Properties for configuring the SphereMesh shape, including dimensions, segmentation, and hemisphere settings.  

height (float): Full height of the sphere. Default: 1.0. Methods: set_height(float) → void, get_height() → float.  
is_hemisphere (bool): If true, a hemisphere is created rather than a full sphere. Default: false. Methods: set_is_hemisphere(bool) → void, get_is_hemisphere() → bool. Note: To get a regular hemisphere, the height and radius of the sphere must be equal.  
radial_segments (int): Number of radial segments on the sphere. Default: 64. Methods: set_radial_segments(int) → void, get_radial_segments() → int.  
radius (float): Radius of sphere. Default: 0.5. Methods: set_radius(float) → void, get_radius() → float.  
rings (int): Number of segments along the height of the sphere. Default: 32. Methods: set_rings(int) → void, get_rings() → int.